AN ACT relating to gaming; revising the definitions of certain terms related to
gaming; providing for the administrative approval of games or
gambling games by the Chair of the Nevada Gaming Control Board;
revising the types of games that may be exposed by gaming
establishments; making a technical correction to refer to a race book
and sports pool for the purposes of licensing an establishment to
operate interactive gaming; removing and repealing provisions
governing cash access and wagering instrument service providers;
removing and repealing provisions governing global risk management;
and providing other matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law defines certain terms for the purposes of provisions relating to gaming.
2 (NRS 463.013-463.01967) [Section 1 of this bill removes dice, playing cards and devices for
3 weighing or counting money from the definition of the term “associated equipment.”] Section
4 4 of this bill adds a person who sells and provides management, or consultation or instruction
5 in the management, of risks associated with wagering pools for a race or sporting event or any
6 other event for which a wager may be accepted to the definition of the term “information
7 service.”
8 Existing law: (1) prohibits, in general, a gaming licensee from offering a game or
9 gambling game for play if the game or gambling game has not received a recommendation
10 from the Nevada Gaming Control Board or an approval from the Nevada Gaming
11 Commission; and (2) requires the Commission to adopt regulations governing the approval of
12 games or gambling games. (NRS 463.164) Section 6 of this bill instead prohibits a gaming
13 licensee from offering a game or gambling game for play if the game or gambling game has
14 not been administratively approved by the Chair of the Board in accordance with regulations
15 adopted by the Commission governing such administrative approval. Section 2 of this bill
16 makes a conforming change to refer to such regulations and administrative approval of a game
17 or gambling game.
18 Existing law prohibits the Commission from approving a license for an establishment to
19 operate interactive gaming unless certain conditions are met. (NRS 463.750) Section 8 of this
20 bill makes a technical correction to refer to a race book and sports pool for purposes of such
21 licensure.

